<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">25</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2005</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">321</span> - <span property="pageEnd">331</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15798052/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">15798052</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2005.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2005</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.252045083">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=GRE+%3D+gradient+echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">GRE = gradient echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HCC+%3D+hepatocellular+carcinoma&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HCC = hepatocellular carcinoma</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">A wide spectrum of hepatic neoplasms may demonstrate intratumoral fatty change—the pattern of which is helpful in differential diagnosis—and MR imaging is the most specific imaging technique for demonstrating both microscopic and macroscopic fat.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Srinivasa R.</span> <span property="familyName">Prasad</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio (S.R.P.); the Department of Pathology and Immunology, Washington University, St Louis, Mo (H.W.); and the Department of Radiology, Mallinckrodt Institute of Radiology, 510 S Kingshighway Blvd, Ninth Floor, St Louis, MO 63110 (H.R., C.O.M., V.R.N., W.D.M., J.P.H.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2002 RSNA Scientific Assembly. Received April 20, 2004; revision requested June 7; revision received and accepted June 30. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Prasad/Srinivasa+R" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Hanlin</span> <span property="familyName">Wang</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio (S.R.P.); the Department of Pathology and Immunology, Washington University, St Louis, Mo (H.W.); and the Department of Radiology, Mallinckrodt Institute of Radiology, 510 S Kingshighway Blvd, Ninth Floor, St Louis, MO 63110 (H.R., C.O.M., V.R.N., W.D.M., J.P.H.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2002 RSN